As rampant looting continues in parts of the Gauteng, the situation in Vosloorus is volatile with looters not backing down. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - As rampant looting continues in parts of the Gauteng, the situation in Vosloorus is volatile with looters not backing down. After cleaning out at least five shopping centres in the last few days, hundreds of looters descended on the Chris Hani Crossing Mall where even law enforcement struggled to contain them. READ: Police presence to be increased in looting hotspots: Cele eNCA's senior reporter Aviwe Mtila was there as the standoff between the police and looters intensified. Watch the video above.